                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1542729137135-research-award-recipients" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#562f3fa0-53c1-46e7-98fb-316dbc86d052" href="#accordion-content-1542729137135-research-award-recipients" aria-controls="accordion-content-1542729137135-research-award-recipients" aria-expanded="false">
                            Research Award Recipients
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1542729137135-research-award-recipients" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1542729137135-research-award-recipients">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1542729137135 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="e556f5d8-04ae-4a4c-91a0-61b634f802f1" >

    <p>Individuals in receipt of a research award involving research work and remuneration offered either by a Canadian academic institution or the individual’s own country or institution, may be invited by a Ryerson University faculty member acting as a host supervisor, to conduct research at Ryerson. The individual must meet a number of conditions, including providing evidence that: </p> 
<ul> 
 <li>through a competitive assessment and review process and based on merit and academic excellence, they are the direct recipient of the award involving work and remuneration</li> 
 <li>they hold an official position or an affiliation or registration with a credible academic or educational institution or agency in their country of citizenship or residence</li> 
 <li>they have academic excellence and expertise in a field related to the particular work to be undertaken, will be able to actively contribute to and benefit the research project and will have a significant role to play or value to add to the research project. The position offered to them must reflect the experience and expertise they bring.<br> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>For more information, please visit <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/corporate/publications-manuals/operational-bulletins-manuals/temporary-residents/foreign-workers/exemption-codes/public-policy-competitiveness-economy.html#post-doc" target="_blank">IRCC<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a>.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#e556f5d8-04ae-4a4c-91a0-61b634f802f1");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1542729137793-short-term--120-day--work-permit-exemption-for-researchers" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#562f3fa0-53c1-46e7-98fb-316dbc86d052" href="#accordion-content-1542729137793-short-term--120-day--work-permit-exemption-for-researchers" aria-controls="accordion-content-1542729137793-short-term--120-day--work-permit-exemption-for-researchers" aria-expanded="false">
                            Short-Term (120-day) Work Permit Exemption for Researchers
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1542729137793-short-term--120-day--work-permit-exemption-for-researchers" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1542729137793-short-term--120-day--work-permit-exemption-for-researchers">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1542729137793 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="33991e1d-29a4-409b-921c-a4eced0208a7" >

    <p>A foreign national outside of Canada, who is able to demonstrate academic excellence or expertise in a field related to the particular work to be undertaken and who has a significant role to play in or value to add to a research project may be invited by a Ryerson University faculty member to conduct research for a maximum of 120 consecutive calendar days, provided that the research work offered reflects their experience and expertise and the role they will play in the project. The 120-day work permit exemption is permitted only once within a 12-month period.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>For up-to-date information, please visit <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/corporate/publications-manuals/operational-bulletins-manuals/temporary-residents/foreign-workers/researcher-exemption.html" target="_blank">IRCC<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a>.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#33991e1d-29a4-409b-921c-a4eced0208a7");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1542729138445-visiting-student-eligibility" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#562f3fa0-53c1-46e7-98fb-316dbc86d052" href="#accordion-content-1542729138445-visiting-student-eligibility" aria-controls="accordion-content-1542729138445-visiting-student-eligibility" aria-expanded="false">
                            Visiting Student Eligibility
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1542729138445-visiting-student-eligibility" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1542729138445-visiting-student-eligibility">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1542729138445 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="78ab348d-1d3c-49e3-aa18-a58d343b5d29" >

    <p>An international visiting student is an individual conducting research at Ryerson University under the supervision of a Ryerson faculty member.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>In addition to meeting the conditions of at least one of the above noted immigration categories, students must meet the following eligibility requirements:&nbsp;</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>be enrolled in a full-time, undergraduate, master’s or doctoral&nbsp; program at a your university in Canada or abroad home institution</li> 
 <li>be in good academic standing</li> 
 <li>have a letter of support from their home academic unit supporting their research visit and proof of enrollment at the home institution</li> 
 <li>have confirmation from both a supporting supervisor from their home institution and a Ryerson faculty member interested in hosting them</li> 
 <li>be proficient in English (both written and verbal)</li> 
 <li>be able to obtain required legal authorization to enter and remain in Canada (including a work permit, if required)</li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#78ab348d-1d3c-49e3-aa18-a58d343b5d29");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>
    </div>
</div>




</div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="bd640650-c99a-4ee6-8296-bab8a5b9d69f" >

    <h2>Obligations of Faculty Hosts</h2> 
<p>Faculty hosts are bound by the following responsibilities and obligations as part of the arrangement to host international researchers:&nbsp;</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Agreeing to supervise and take responsibility for an international visiting researcher during the full period of the visitor’s stay</li> 
 <li>Being prepared to work with the researcher, Human Resources, and the respective Research Administrative Support Officer, and any other relevant office/individuals to support the development and signature of necessary documentation, taking into consideration research activity-related policies and procedures such as terms for research granting agencies, intellectual property, and research ethics approval as appropriate</li> 
 <li>Ensuring compliance at all times with the <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/senate/PoliciesAlpha/">University’s policies</a> on Ownership of Student Work in Research and <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/research/resources/ethics/">policies on Research Ethics involving subjects and animals</a></li> 
 <li>Arranging for orientations to labs and facilities and providing workplace safety training, including mandatory online EHS training for all research students</li> 
 <li>Sending timely notification to <a href="mailto:visitingresearch@ryerson.ca">visitingresearch@ryerson.ca</a><span> of any changes to the conditions of the visiting researcher’s stay on campus (funding, research project, time period, etc)</span></li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#bd640650-c99a-4ee6-8296-bab8a5b9d69f");});</script></div>

				

				
