                            Financial Support
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1542730047194-financial-support" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1542730047194-financial-support">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1542730047194 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="4ea5188b-f70f-4330-99a3-5e97d077d2a9" >

    <p>Please note that Visiting Research Scholars/Professors who will receive funding directly from Ryerson are considered research staff and are processed by HR. You will be financially responsible for the benefits and vacation pay incurred, and the visitor will receive pay net of statutory Canadian payroll deductions.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>If you wish to support your visiting researcher through a research grant, you will need to first ensure that it will be an eligible expense under your grant. Note that many granting agencies employ very restrictive terms and conditions on their funding.</p> 
<p>For funding by the Tri-Council Agencies (NSERC, SSHRC, CIHR), please refer to the <a href="http://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/Professors-Professeurs/FinancialAdminGuide-GuideAdminFinancier/index_eng.asp" target="_blank">Tri-Agency Financial Administration Guide<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a>.&nbsp;If you require assistance in determining expense eligibility, please consult with your Research Grant Officer as appropriate. Researchers receiving financial support from the University must obtain a Canadian temporary work permit and Social Insurance Number (SIN) to facilitate the payment of the funds by the University.</p>
    





</div>
